---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout
  title="Gold Weight: Troy Ounces Explained"
  description="Why gold uses a different ounce system. Understand troy ounces vs regular ounces and how gold is weighed."
  keywords="troy ounce, gold weight, troy vs avoirdupois, gold ounce, precious metals weight, troy ounce grams"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Weight</span>
      </nav>

      <BlogCrossLinks title="Gold Weight: Troy Ounces Explained" />

      <!-- Article Meta -->
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2025-06-15">June 15, 2025</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Lead Paragraph -->
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">
        When gold is priced at "$2,000 per ounce," it is not the same ounce you use in cooking. Gold, silver, and other precious metals use the troy ounce — a heavier, older unit. Here is why, and how to convert.
      </p>

      <!-- Section: Troy vs Regular -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Troy Ounce vs Regular Ounce</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-6 my-6 not-prose shadow-sm">
        <div class="space-y-2 text-center">
          <p class="text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">1 troy ounce = 31.103 grams</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">1 regular (avoirdupois) ounce = 28.349 grams</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">A troy ounce is about 10% heavier than a regular ounce</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Why Troy? -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why Use a Different System?</h2>
      <p>The troy system dates back to medieval Troyes, France — a major trading hub. It persists because:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>The precious metals market is global and centuries old</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>Changing units would cause chaos in contracts and pricing</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>All international gold trading uses troy ounces by convention</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>It provides a standardised measure everyone in the industry understands</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section: Key Conversions -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Key Conversions</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>1 troy ounce = 31.1035 grams</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>1 troy ounce = 1.097 regular ounces</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>1 troy pound = 12 troy ounces (not 16 like regular pounds)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>1 kilogram = 32.15 troy ounces</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>1 gold bar (standard) = 400 troy ounces ≈ 12.4 kg</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section: Practical Context -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Putting It in Context</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Gold coin (1 oz):</strong> 31.1g — about the weight of 6 UK pound coins</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Gold bar (1 kg):</strong> 32.15 troy oz — fits in your palm but weighs as much as a bag of sugar</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Olympic gold medal:</strong> Only ~6g of actual gold (the rest is silver)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Converter CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-orange-50 dark:from-amber-900/20 dark:to-orange-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">
            🔗 Try our free weight converter
          </p>
          <a
            href="/convert/weight"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm"
          >
            Open Converter →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Back to Blog -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">
          ← Back to all articles
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
